{
  "stem": "5356.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were-- we were-- and this was from the day when they sent everybody away until January the 10, I think.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We worked, we were there, you know, to gathered a lot of stuff from the houses and the Germans sold it to the Poles and things like that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was 1942.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then in-- in end of December--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the-- my father died in 1941.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He died of-- I mean, things were-- my brother was killed, so this took a toll off him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Moshe, which was in the Polish army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was 71 years old-- 72-- I think he was 71 or 72-- when he died.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this took a toll off him and the war with everything, so he was lucky that he died.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We buried him the same day and were able to have services in the house for him and to say kaddish for him the whole year.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then, you know, when-- when this happened, after they sent everybody away, the only left at home was myself in the house, my other brother, Schmuel Meir, and Benjamin, and my sister.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My--my mother and my [INAUDIBLE] in the assembly place, the same as I was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were-- you know, after they picked us out, they remained there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they went with the whole-- with all other peoples that were marched away in the--",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, but we found out afterwards.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A few days later, somebody escaped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they said they took him to Treblinka and what's happening to them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That they were killing them there, gassing them there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So after this happened, you know, we were left in [INAUDIBLE] for those-- I mean, November and December.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the Germans announced they're forming a second ghetto in Sandomierz.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
